# UI Library Decision

**Date:** December 10, 2025
**Status:** DECIDED
**Selected:** Blueprint JS 6.x

---

## Decision Summary

After evaluating multiple options, **Blueprint JS 6.x** was selected for the MMS frontend.

### Why Blueprint JS

| Factor | Blueprint JS |
| ------ | ------------ |
| React compatibility | React 18 (required) |
| Enterprise appearance | Professional, data-dense |
| Data table | Built-in Table component |
| Form components | Complete set |
| TypeScript | First-class support |
| Date pickers | Built-in DatePicker |
| Documentation | Comprehensive |

### Why Not Other Options

| Library | Reason Not Selected |
| ------- | ------------------- |
| Cloudscape | SSR compatibility issues |
| shadcn/ui | Requires more assembly |
| MUI | Bundle size, Material design |
| Ant Design | Chinese documentation bias |

---

## Current Stack

| Layer | Technology |
| ----- | ---------- |
| Meta Framework | Astro 5.x |
| UI Framework | React 18.x |
| UI Library | Blueprint JS 6.x |
| Styling | Blueprint CSS |

### Blueprint Packages Used

```
@blueprintjs/core        # Core components
@blueprintjs/icons       # Icon set
@blueprintjs/select      # Select components
@blueprintjs/table       # Data tables
@blueprintjs/datetime    # Date/time pickers
```

---

## React 18 Requirement

Blueprint JS 6.x officially supports React 18, not React 19. The monorepo was configured to use React 18 for compatibility.

**Important:** Do not upgrade to React 19 without verifying Blueprint compatibility.

